# Next.js Development Patterns

## App Router Structure

- Use the App Router pattern with [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx) as the root layout
- Place page components in [app/page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx) and other route files
- Global styles are defined in [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css)

## Configuration Files

- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration with TypeScript
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration for Next.js
- [postcss.config.mjs](mdc:postcss.config.mjs) - PostCSS configuration for Tailwind CSS

## Styling

- Use Tailwind CSS for styling (configured in [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css))
- Follow the design system defined in [registry/domino/ui/](mdc:registry/domino/ui/)

## Performance

- Implement proper loading states and error boundaries
- Use Next.js Image component for optimized images
- Implement proper SEO meta tags in layout and page components
- Use dynamic imports for code splitting when appropriate

## Development Workflow

- Use the development server with `npm run dev`
- Hot reloading is enabled for development
- Check [package.json](mdc:package.json) for available scripts
